But Lucr. has evidently taken καρδία 111 its usual sense: such a mistake was not unlikely to occur3 but it has caused him sadly to misrepresent the case: he makes the disease not merely descend into the breast, but wholly fill the breast, and stream together into the sad heart, and thus at the very commencement of its course force all the fastnesses of life, though the patients afterwards go through many stages of suffering and live at least eight or nine days : Thuc. says some sentences later διεξῄει γὰρ διὰ παντὸς τοῦ σώματος ἄνωθεν ἀρξάμενον τὸ ἐν τῇ κεφαλῇ πρῶτον ἱδρυ- θὲν κακόν.
